---
/**
 * /legal/terms — Terms of Service.
 *
 * First-draft pre-launch terms (2026-05-13). Required so the platform can
 * lawfully collect phone numbers and emails for OTP login. NZ Privacy Act
 * 2020 is the primary regime; the platform is global so we also acknowledge
 * GDPR, UK GDPR, CCPA, and the Australian Privacy Act 1988.
 *
 * Flagged for NZ-licensed lawyer review before public launch:
 *   - NZBN placeholder (TODO when Tournamental Holdings registration is
 *     confirmed).
 *   - Wellington venue clause (the registered office is TBD).
 *   - The legal@tournamental.com mailbox is a placeholder.
 *   - The Drips Network revenue-share clauses are summaries of doc 19;
 *     a tax lawyer should check the "not employment / no withholding"
 *     language for NZ + US recipients.
 *   - Liability cap is set to NZD 100; sense-check this against NZ
 *     Consumer Guarantees Act carve-outs.
 *
 * Cache policy: long-cache static HTML. The edge ingress reads the
 * data-cache-control attribute and sets the real header.
 */
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="Terms of Service · Tournamental"
  description="The legal terms governing use of Tournamental, the open-source tournament prediction platform run by Tournamental Holdings."
  ogImage="/og/legal.png"
>
  {/* Long-cache by default; bumps automatically when the file content
      hash changes thanks to the cloudflared edge reading
      data-cache-control. */}
  <article
    class="container-prose pt-16 pb-20 prose-vt"
    data-cache-control="public, max-age=3600, s-maxage=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800"
  >
    <p class="text-ink-500 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-2">
      Terms of Service
    </h1>
    <p class="text-ink-500 text-sm mt-3">
      Last updated: 13 May 2026. This is a pre-launch first draft pending
      review by a New Zealand licensed lawyer. If anything here conflicts
      with applicable law, the law wins and the rest stays in force.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6">
      Welcome to Tournamental. These Terms of Service (the
      <strong>Terms</strong>) govern your access to and use of the
      Tournamental platform, including the marketing site at
      <code>tournamental.com</code>, the play app at
      <code>play.tournamental.com</code>, the API at
      <code>api.tournamental.com</code>, the Telegram bot
      <code>@TournamentalBot</code>, the open-source repositories at
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental">github.com/0800tim/tournamental</a>,
      and any other surface we operate (collectively, the
      <strong>Platform</strong>).
    </p>

    <h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
    <p>
      By creating an account, signing in with a phone number or email
      one-time code, submitting a prediction, posting content, sharing a
      bracket, joining a syndicate, embedding a Tournamental widget on
      a third-party site, calling our API with a token issued to you,
      or otherwise using the Platform, you agree to these Terms. If you
      do not agree, do not use the Platform.
    </p>
    <p>
      These Terms form a contract between you and Tournamental
      Holdings. They apply to every interaction you have with the
      Platform, whether you are a registered user, a casual visitor
      reading a shared bracket, a journalist accessing the press kit,
      a contributor pushing pull requests against the open-source
      repository, or a partner integrating with our affiliate router.
      Different sections may apply more or less to each kind of user;
      where a section only applies in one context, we say so.
    </p>
    <p>
      We may post additional terms for specific features (for example,
      future entry-fee pools, affiliate-router placements, or the
      tournament-organiser tier). Those additional terms form part of
      these Terms when you opt into the feature they cover. If there is
      a direct conflict, the feature-specific terms control for that
      feature only; everything else in these Terms keeps running in the
      background.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Tournamental Holdings</strong> is a New Zealand company
      operating the Platform.
      {/* NZBN: TODO insert when company registration confirmed. */}
      Our registered office is in Wellington, New Zealand
      {/* TODO: update with the registered street address once filed. */}.
      You can contact us at
      <a class="link" href="mailto:0800tim@gmail.com">0800tim@gmail.com</a>
      (launch contact) or
      <a class="link" href="mailto:legal@tournamental.com">legal@tournamental.com</a>
      {/* TODO: mailbox provisioning */}.
    </p>

    <h2>3. What Tournamental is</h2>
    <p>
      Tournamental is an open-source tournament prediction platform. We
      let people predict outcomes of sports tournaments, watch matches
      play out in a 3D in-browser renderer, run syndicates (friend
      groups) with their own leaderboards, and share predictions to
      social media as cards and clips.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Platform code is licensed under the Apache License, Version
      2.0. Our documentation is licensed under Creative Commons
      Attribution 4.0 (CC-BY 4.0). The full licence texts ship with the
      repository at
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/LICENSE">LICENSE</a>
      and
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/LICENSE-DOCS">docs/LICENSE-DOCS</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Tournamental name, the Tournamental "V" mark, the affiliate
      codes, and the operational accounts on social platforms are
      proprietary to Tournamental Holdings. Apache 2.0 covers the code,
      not the brand. If you fork the code, please fork it under a
      different name.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Eligibility</h2>
    <p>
      You must be at least 13 years old to use the Platform. If your
      local law (for example, the GDPR child-consent threshold in your
      EU member state) sets a higher minimum age for using online
      services without parental consent, you must meet that higher age.
      In some jurisdictions that means 14, 15, or 16; we adopt the
      higher of 13 and the local minimum.
    </p>
    <p>
      Some features may carry their own age gates. The on-chain
      prize-pool feature contemplated by our roadmap (see
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/21-onchain-sweepstakes-oracle.md">doc 21</a>)
      will only be available to users who are at least the local minimum
      gambling age (commonly 18 or 21) and resident in a jurisdiction
      where such participation is lawful. We will gate these features by
      country at the network edge and by self-attestation at the
      account level.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Accounts</h2>
    <p>
      You sign in with a phone number or email address using a one-time
      code (OTP). Phone codes are delivered via SMS or WhatsApp through
      our delivery partner Aiva SMS. Email codes are delivered via our
      auth provider Supabase. By providing your phone number or email
      you authorise us to send you one-time codes to that address;
      standard message rates from your carrier may apply. Telegram
      sign-in via the Tournamental bot is an alternative path that does
      not require us to learn your phone number; the same account
      identity is bound to whichever channel you first verified with.
    </p>
    <p>
      You are responsible for keeping your account secure, for the picks
      you submit, for the handle (display name) you choose, and for any
      content you publish on the Platform. One account per person.
      Impersonating another person, including any public figure, is a
      ground for immediate suspension under section 14. If you suspect
      your account has been compromised, request a sign-out from all
      devices at <code>/profile/security</code> and re-verify with a
      fresh OTP; we will rotate the underlying session secret for you.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can change your handle at any time, subject to a short
      rate-limit and the rule that handles cannot be transferred for
      consideration. We reserve handles that are confusingly similar to
      Tournamental Holdings, to staff handles, to high-profile
      sportspeople and clubs, or to officially licensed competitions.
      Where a third party has a stronger trade-mark claim to a handle
      than the user who currently holds it, we will resolve the dispute
      in good faith and may require the user to pick a different
      handle.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree not to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Scrape or mirror the Platform at industrial scale. The site
        is open source; the data isn't. Our Cloudflare Web Application
        Firewall will block aggressive scraping automatically.</li>
      <li>Create accounts in an automated way, run a bot net of fake
        users, or otherwise game leaderboards. Our humanness-score
        system (see <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/20-identity-and-humanness.md">doc 20</a>) is designed to detect this.</li>
      <li>Post content that is illegal in your jurisdiction or ours,
        including content that infringes another person's intellectual
        property, harasses or threatens others, contains malware, or
        depicts the sexual abuse of children.</li>
      <li>Use the share-card or clip-share pipeline to distribute
        political advertising, hate speech, doxxing material, or any
        content designed primarily to cause harm.</li>
      <li>Reverse-engineer the Platform to bypass paid features,
        anti-cheat measures, or rate-limits. The code is open source;
        run your own copy under a different name if you want a
        different policy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. User content</h2>
    <p>
      You retain ownership of everything you create on the Platform:
      your picks, your bracket, your handle, your avatar, your syndicate
      name, and any text or images you upload. You grant Tournamental
      Holdings a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, sublicensable
      licence to host, store, reproduce, modify (only for the purposes
      of resizing, transcoding, and re-encoding for delivery), display,
      perform, and distribute your content within the Platform's own
      surfaces and the official Tournamental accounts on social media.
    </p>
    <p>
      This licence exists so we can do the things that make the Platform
      work, for example showing your bracket on
      <code>/s/&lt;guid&gt;</code>, generating an Open Graph card from
      your picks, including your handle in leaderboards, and creating a
      30-second goal clip with you tagged. It does not extend to using
      your content in paid advertising without your separate consent.
    </p>
    <p>
      You represent that you own or have the necessary rights to the
      content you submit and that posting it does not violate any third
      party's rights. We may remove content that, in our reasonable
      view, breaches these Terms or any law.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Money, pools, and what we do (and don't) do</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Tournamental is a platform and a game.</strong> We exist
      to gamify the tournament; we do not take bets, we do not handle
      money, and we are not a sportsbook. Points and leaderboard
      placement are for fun and bragging rights.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>We never handle payments, cash, or prizes.</strong>
      Tournamental does not collect, hold, process, or pay out any money
      (entry fees, pots, vouchers, or otherwise), and we never fulfil or
      guarantee any prize. Every payment, cash pot, voucher, and prize, and
      every promise to award one, is solely the responsibility of the pool
      or syndicate administrator and any sponsoring brand. They alone must
      collect any money and ensure that any advertised prize genuinely
      exists and is honoured.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Pools and entry fees.</strong> The Platform lets pool
      administrators (the person who created the pool) run a private
      or public pool for their friends, members, or audience. If a
      pool administrator chooses to charge an entry fee, take a real-
      money pot, or award a cash or in-kind prize, <strong>that
      arrangement is between the pool administrator and the people who
      join</strong>. Tournamental is not a party to those transactions.
      We do not collect, hold, escrow, or disburse those funds. We do
      not verify that any advertised prize exists, has been funded, or
      will be paid. We make no representation that any pool will pay
      out. If a pool administrator fails to pay, your recourse is with
      them, not with Tournamental.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>We strongly recommend NOT joining a public paid-entry
      pool.</strong> A public pool is open to strangers, and the same
      reasoning that makes private pools work (you know the administrator
      personally; you trust them to handle the cash) doesn't apply. We
      provide no payment rails, no escrow, no dispute resolution, and
      no guarantee that anyone will pay anyone. Joining a public paid-
      entry pool is at your own risk. Pool administrators who advertise
      paid entry or prizes on a public pool are doing so on their own
      authority; nothing they say binds Tournamental.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Odds, prediction markets, and affiliate links.</strong>
      The Platform may surface odds, lines, or prices from third-party
      prediction markets and sportsbooks (for example, Polymarket).
      Some of those links may carry an affiliate code so we receive a
      referral payment if you sign up. We don't endorse any specific
      operator, we don't recommend gambling, and we don't tell you to
      bet. We surface those numbers because they are useful inputs to a
      prediction game. If you choose to follow an outbound link, your
      relationship from that point is between you and the third-party
      operator under their terms, in their jurisdiction. Tournamental is
      not the broker, the bookmaker, the dealer, or the counter-party
      to any wager.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Future on-platform paid features.</strong> A future paid
      feature (the on-chain prize pool contemplated by
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/21-onchain-sweepstakes-oracle.md">doc 21</a>
      and the affiliate router in
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/18-affiliate-router.md">doc 18</a>)
      may involve real money. Before any such feature goes live we will
      publish supplemental terms, comply with the licensing regime of
      each jurisdiction we operate in, and refuse onboarding to users
      in jurisdictions where the feature would be unlawful. Nothing in
      these Terms entitles you to participate in a paid feature that is
      illegal where you live.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Open source and plugins</h2>
    <p>
      The Tournamental code is open source under Apache 2.0. Contributions
      to the repository are governed by the
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>
      guide and the Developer Certificate of Origin
      (<a class="link" href="https://developercertificate.org/">DCO</a>);
      every commit must carry a <code>Signed-off-by</code> line.
    </p>
    <p>
      Third parties can author plugins to the Platform under the plugin
      architecture documented in
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/28-plugin-architecture.md">doc 28</a>.
      A third-party plugin is the work of its author, not of
      Tournamental Holdings. We do not endorse third-party plugins. We
      may ban any plugin from the Platform if, in our reasonable view,
      it harms users, breaches these Terms, or is unlawful in a
      jurisdiction where the Platform operates. A malicious plugin can
      be removed without prior notice.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Drips Network revenue share</h2>
    <p>
      Contributors whose pull requests are merged into the official
      Tournamental repositories may be eligible for a slice of Platform
      revenue, paid via the
      <a class="link" href="https://www.drips.network/">Drips Network</a>
      smart contracts on Ethereum L1 or an L2 we designate. The split is
      defined on chain and publicly auditable. See
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/19-open-source-and-contributor-revenue.md">doc 19</a>
      for the full mechanics.
    </p>
    <p>
      Receiving a Drips share for a merged contribution is not
      employment, is not a partnership, is not a joint venture, and does
      not create any agency relationship between you and Tournamental
      Holdings. You are responsible for your own tax obligations in
      respect of any value you receive. Tournamental Holdings does not
      withhold tax on Drips payouts and has no employer or contractor
      obligation to do so under this arrangement.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      The affiliate router described in
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/0800tim/tournamental/blob/main/docs/18-affiliate-router.md">doc 18</a>
      routes outbound clicks to licensed sportsbook partners. When you
      click an affiliate link, the destination operator's own terms,
      privacy policy, and regulatory framework apply to anything you do
      on their site. We do not facilitate any wager, do not handle any
      stake, and do not take a share of your stake or your winnings; our
      revenue from the partner is a fixed referral commission disclosed
      in doc 18.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can choose to disable affiliate routing in your account
      preferences. Disabling it does not affect any other Platform
      feature.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p>
      The Platform is provided "as is" and "as available". To the
      maximum extent permitted by law, we make no warranties of any
      kind, whether express, implied, or statutory, including any
      warranty of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
      title, non-infringement, accuracy, or availability.
    </p>
    <p>
      Specifically:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not warrant that the Platform will be uninterrupted,
        error-free, or available at any particular time.</li>
      <li>We do not warrant that fixture data (kick-off times, lineups,
        scores) is correct, complete, or current. Fixture data comes
        from third-party providers and can be wrong.</li>
      <li>We do not warrant the 3D renderer's depiction of any match;
        it is an interpretation of event data, not a broadcast.</li>
      <li>We do not warrant the security of any third-party site you
        reach via an affiliate link.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Nothing in this section limits any non-excludable consumer
      guarantee you have under the New Zealand Consumer Guarantees Act
      1993, the Australian Consumer Law, or equivalent legislation in
      your jurisdiction.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, the total aggregate
      liability of Tournamental Holdings to you under or in connection
      with these Terms and your use of the Platform is limited to the
      greater of
      <strong>NZD 100</strong> or the amount you paid us in the twelve
      months immediately before the event giving rise to the claim. We
      are not liable for any indirect, consequential, special,
      incidental, exemplary, or punitive damages, lost profits, lost
      goodwill, or lost data, however caused.
    </p>
    <p>
      Where applicable consumer law does not permit the above limit, the
      limit is reduced to the minimum permitted by that law and the
      rest of this section remains in force.
    </p>

    <h2>13a. Force majeure</h2>
    <p>
      Neither party is liable for any failure to perform under these
      Terms to the extent that the failure is caused by events outside
      that party's reasonable control, including but not limited to
      acts of god, natural disasters, war, terrorism, civil unrest,
      pandemic, internet-backbone outages, sub-processor failures, or
      government action. The affected party will use reasonable
      efforts to resume performance as soon as practicable.
    </p>

    <h2>13b. No professional advice</h2>
    <p>
      Nothing on the Platform is investment advice, financial advice,
      legal advice, or professional advice of any other kind. The
      predictions, leaderboards, commentary, and statistical analyses
      we publish are for entertainment. Do not treat them as a basis
      for placing a bet, making an investment, or taking any other
      consequential decision. If you need advice, talk to a licensed
      professional.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Termination</h2>
    <p>
      You can stop using the Platform at any time and request deletion
      of your account by emailing
      <a class="link" href="mailto:privacy@tournamental.com">privacy@tournamental.com</a>
      or using the data-export and deletion page in your profile (under
      construction; see Privacy Policy section 8).
    </p>
    <p>
      We can suspend or terminate your account if, in our reasonable
      view, you have breached these Terms, broken the law, or put
      other users at risk. For a serious or repeat breach, we may
      suspend immediately. For a minor or first breach, we will
      generally give you notice and a chance to fix the issue first.
    </p>

    <h2>15. Indemnification</h2>
    <p>
      You agree to indemnify Tournamental Holdings, its officers,
      employees, and contributors against any third-party claim arising
      out of content you contribute to the Platform that infringes that
      third party's intellectual-property, privacy, or publicity rights.
      This indemnity is narrow: it covers the content claim, the
      reasonable cost of defending it, and any settlement we agree to
      with you; it does not cover claims caused by our own conduct or
      claims you can show we are independently responsible for. We
      will tell you about a covered claim within a reasonable time of
      receiving it, give you the opportunity to defend it at your own
      expense, and not settle it without your prior consent except
      where settlement is the only commercially reasonable response.
    </p>

    <h2>15a. Notice and takedown</h2>
    <p>
      If you believe content on the Platform infringes your rights,
      send a written notice to
      <a class="link" href="mailto:legal@tournamental.com">legal@tournamental.com</a>
      identifying the content (URL plus a short description), the
      right you claim, and your contact details. We will assess in
      good faith and, where the claim is well founded, remove the
      content or restrict access to it. We may also notify the user
      who posted the content so they can submit a counter-notice.
      Misuse of this process is itself a breach of these Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>16. Governing law and venue</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by the laws of New Zealand. The courts
      of Wellington, New Zealand have non-exclusive jurisdiction to
      hear any dispute under or in connection with these Terms.
      {/* TODO: replace Wellington with the registered office once filed. */}
    </p>
    <p>
      Nothing in this section prevents you from bringing a claim in
      your local consumer-protection forum where local law requires us
      to accept that forum (for example, EU consumers under the
      Brussels I Recast Regulation).
    </p>

    <h2>17. Changes to these Terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these Terms from time to time. For a material
      change, we will give at least 30 days' notice by email (to the
      address on your account) and via an on-site banner on the
      marketing site and the play app. The "Last updated" date at the
      top of the page reflects the most recent change. Continued use of
      the Platform after the notice period means you accept the new
      Terms. If you do not accept, you can close your account before
      the new Terms take effect.
    </p>

    <h2>18. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      General: <a class="link" href="mailto:0800tim@gmail.com">0800tim@gmail.com</a>
      (launch contact)
      or <a class="link" href="mailto:hello@tournamental.com">hello@tournamental.com</a>.
      Privacy: <a class="link" href="mailto:privacy@tournamental.com">privacy@tournamental.com</a>.
      Legal: <a class="link" href="mailto:legal@tournamental.com">legal@tournamental.com</a>.
      Security: <a class="link" href="mailto:security@tournamental.com">security@tournamental.com</a>.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-10 border-ink-700/70" />

    <p class="text-ink-500 text-sm">
      Companion documents:
      <a class="link" href="/legal/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
      ·
      <a class="link" href="/legal/cookies">Cookie Notice</a>
      ·
      <a class="link" href="/legal">Legal hub</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
